<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Cookie vs JWT Comparison - DevAuth</title>
  <style>
    * {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }
    
    body {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
      background: #3B3B3B;
      min-height: 100vh;
      padding: 20px;
      color: #ffffff;
    }
    
    .header {
      text-align: center;
      color: white;
      margin-bottom: 30px;
    }
    
    .header h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      color: #00F7FF;
      text-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 247, 255, 0.5);
    }
    
    .header p {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      opacity: 0.9;
      color: #d1d5db;
    }
    
    .comparison-container {
      max-width: 1400px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 20px;
    }
    
    .auth-method {
      background: #2a2a2a;
      border-radius: 15px;
      padding: 30px;
      box-shadow: 0 10px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
      border: 2px solid #4a4a4a;
    }
    
    .method-header {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 25px;
      padding-bottom: 20px;
      border-bottom: 3px solid;
    }
    
    .jwt-method {
      border-color: #A78BFA;
    }
    
    .jwt-method .method-header {
      border-color: #A78BFA;
    }
    
    .cookie-method {
      border-color: #00F7FF;
    }
    
    .cookie-method .method-header {
      border-color: #00F7FF;
    }
    
    .method-icon {
      font-size: 3rem;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    
    .method-title {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 5px;
      color: #ffffff;
    }
    
    .method-subtitle {
      color: #d1d5db;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }
    
    .info-section {
      margin-bottom: 25px;
    }
    
    .info-section h3 {
      color: #A78BFA;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
    }
    
    .info-list {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
    }
    
    .info-list li {
      padding: 10px;
      background: rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.05);
      border-radius: 6px;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      display: flex;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 10px;
      color: #d1d5db;
      border: 1px solid #4a4a4a;
    }
    
    .info-list li:before {
      content: "‚úì";
      color: #00F7FF;
      font-weight: bold;
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }
    
    .info-list li strong {
      color: #A78BFA;
    }
    
    .pros-cons {
      display: grid;
      gap: 15px;
    }
    
    .pros, .cons {
      padding: 15px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      border-left: 4px solid;
    }
    
    .pros {
      background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.1);
      border-left-color: #10b981;
    }
    
    .cons {
      background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.1);
      border-left-color: #ef4444;
    }
    
    .pros h4, .cons h4 {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      font-size: 1rem;
      color: #ffffff;
    }
    
    .pros ul, .cons ul {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
    }
    
    .pros li, .cons li {
      padding: 5px 0;
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      color: #d1d5db;
    }
    
    .pros li:before {
      content: "‚úì ";
      color: #10b981;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    
    .cons li:before {
      content: "‚úó ";
      color: #ef4444;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    
    .test-buttons {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 10px;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }
    
    .btn {
      padding: 15px;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 8px;
      font-size: 1rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: all 0.3s;
      text-decoration: none;
      text-align: center;
      display: block;
    }
    
    .btn-jwt {
      background: #A78BFA;
      color: #3B3B3B;
      box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.3);
    }
    
    .btn-jwt:hover {
      background: #9333ea;
      transform: translateY(-2px);
      box-shadow: 0 0 30px rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.5);
    }
    
    .btn-cookie {
      background: #00F7FF;
      color: #3B3B3B;
      box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 247, 255, 0.3);
    }
    
    .btn-cookie:hover {
      background: #00d4db;
      transform: translateY(-2px);
      box-shadow: 0 0 30px rgba(0, 247, 255, 0.5);
    }
    
    .back-link {
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }
    
    .back-link a {
      color: #A78BFA;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-size: 1rem;
      padding: 10px 20px;
      background: rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.1);
      border-radius: 8px;
      display: inline-block;
      border: 1px solid #4a4a4a;
      transition: all 0.3s;
    }
    
    .back-link a:hover {
      background: rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.2);
      border-color: #A78BFA;
    }

    @media (max-width: 1024px) {
      .comparison-container {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="header">
    <h1>üîê Cookie vs JWT Authentication</h1>
    <p>Compare session-based and token-based authentication side-by-side</p>
  </div>

  <div class="comparison-container">
    <!-- JWT Method -->
    <div class="auth-method jwt-method">
      <div class="method-header">
        <div class="method-icon">üé´</div>
        <h2 class="method-title">JWT (Token-Based)</h2>
        <p class="method-subtitle">Stateless Authentication</p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-section">
        <h3>üìã How It Works</h3>
        <ul class="info-list">
          <li>Server generates a JWT token</li>
          <li>Client stores token (localStorage or cookie)</li>
          <li>Client sends token in Authorization header</li>
          <li>Server validates token signature</li>
          <li>No server-side session storage needed</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="info-section">
        <h3>üîç Technical Details</h3>
        <ul class="info-list">
          <li><strong>Storage:</strong> Client-side (usually localStorage)</li>
          <li><strong>Validation:</strong> Cryptographic signature</li>
          <li><strong>Server State:</strong> Stateless (no DB lookup)</li>
          <li><strong>Scalability:</strong> Excellent (no session store)</li>
          <li><strong>Header:</strong> Authorization: Bearer TOKEN</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="pros-cons">
        <div class="pros">
          <h4>‚úì Advantages</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>No server-side storage required</li>
            <li>Works across multiple servers easily</li>
            <li>Can be used across different domains</li>
            <li>Contains user info in the token</li>
            <li>Perfect for microservices</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="cons">
          <h4>‚úó Disadvantages</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Can't easily revoke tokens</li>
            <li>Larger than session IDs (more bandwidth)</li>
            <li>Token visible in localStorage (XSS risk)</li>
            <li>Payload visible (not encrypted, just encoded)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="test-buttons">
        <a href="/login/google" class="btn btn-jwt">
          Test JWT Flow ‚Üí
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Cookie Method -->
    <div class="auth-method cookie-method">
      <div class="method-header">
        <div class="method-icon">üç™</div>
        <h2 class="method-title">Cookie (Session-Based)</h2>
        <p class="method-subtitle">Stateful Authentication</p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-section">
        <h3>üìã How It Works</h3>
        <ul class="info-list">
          <li>Server creates session on login</li>
          <li>Session ID stored in httpOnly cookie</li>
          <li>Browser automatically sends cookie</li>
          <li>Server looks up session in database</li>
          <li>Session data stored server-side</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="info-section">
        <h3>üîç Technical Details</h3>
        <ul class="info-list">
          <li><strong>Storage:</strong> Server-side (Redis, DB, memory)</li>
          <li><strong>Validation:</strong> Session ID lookup</li>
          <li><strong>Server State:</strong> Stateful (requires session store)</li>
          <li><strong>Scalability:</strong> Requires shared session store</li>
          <li><strong>Cookie Flags:</strong> httpOnly, secure, sameSite</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="pros-cons">
        <div class="pros">
          <h4>‚úì Advantages</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>httpOnly cookies prevent XSS attacks</li>
            <li>Easy to revoke sessions instantly</li>
            <li>Small cookie size (just session ID)</li>
            <li>Browser handles cookies automatically</li>
            <li>More secure for traditional web apps</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="cons">
          <h4>‚úó Disadvantages</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Requires server-side storage (memory/DB)</li>
            <li>Harder to scale horizontally</li>
            <li>CSRF protection needed</li>
            <li>Requires session lookup on every request</li>
            <li>Cookies don't work well with mobile apps</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="test-buttons">
        <a href="/login-cookie/google" class="btn btn-cookie">
          Test Cookie Flow ‚Üí
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="back-link">
    <a href="/">‚Üê Back to Home</a>
  </div>
</body>
</html>